Berdasarkan tutorial kemarin, paman bikin script ini:

```#!/usr/bin/env bash

### -- config -- 

# $token variable here in config.sh
config_file=~/.config/cupubot/config.sh

if [ ! -f $config_file ];
then
    echo "Config not found!" && exit 0
else
    source $config_file
fi

tele_url="https://api.telegram.org/bot${token}"

### -- main -- 

updates=$(curl -s "${tele_url}/getUpdates")
count_update=$(echo $updates | jq -r ".result | length") 
    
for ((i=0; i<$count_update; i++)); do
    update=$(echo $updates | jq -r ".result[$i]")
    echo "$update
"
done```
Mengenai config sudah dibahas kemarin, tempat untuk token.

Sekarang kita bikin ada section. Ada bagian2. Dan masukkan bagian yang panjang dalam fungsi.

**02-main-single.bash**

```#!/usr/bin/env bash

### -- config -- 

# $token variable here in config.sh
config_file=~/.config/cupubot/config.sh

if [ ! -f $config_file ];
then
    echo "Config not found!" && exit 0
else
    source $config_file
fi

tele_url="https://api.telegram.org/bot${token}"

### -- task -- 

function process_observe() {
  local i update
    local updates=$(curl -s "${tele_url}/getUpdates")
    local count_update=$(echo $updates | jq -r ".result | length") 
    
    for ((i=0; i<$count_update; i++)); do
        update=$(echo $updates | jq -r ".result[$i]")
        echo "$update
"
    done
}

### -- controller --

function do_observe() {
  # no loop
    process_observe
} 

### -- main --

do_observe
```

Yang pertama adalah `main` script.

```#!/usr/bin/env bash
# This is a telegram bot in bash

### -- module --

DIR=$(dirname "$0")
. ${DIR}/03-config.bash
. ${DIR}/03-controller.bash
. ${DIR}/03-task-observe.bash

### -- main --

do_observe```

Main script **harus** memakai `sha-bang`, sedangkan script yang lain tidak harus memakai `sha-bang` atau `#!`.

**03-controller.bash**

function do_observe() {
    process_observe
}```

Terakhir `task` dari `observe` itu sendiri.

**03-task-observe.bash**

```#!/usr/bin/env bash

function process_observe() {
  local i update
    local updates=$(curl -s "${tele_url}/getUpdates")
    local count_update=$(echo $updates | jq -r ".result | length") 
    
    for ((i=0; i<$count_update; i++)); do
        update=$(echo $updates | jq -r ".result[$i]")
        echo "$update
"
    done
}```

**05-task-reply**

```#!/usr/bin/env bash

function process_reply() {
  # global-project : last_id
  # global-module  : _
  local i update message_id chat_id text

    local updates=$(curl -s "${tele_url}/getUpdates?offset=$last_id")
    local count_update=$(echo $updates | jq -r ".result | length") 
    
    [[ $count_update -eq 0 ]] && echo -n "."

    for ((i=0; i<$count_update; i++)); do
        update=$(echo $updates | jq -r ".result[$i]")   
        last_id=$(echo $update | jq -r ".update_id")     
        message_id=$(echo $update | jq -r ".message.message_id")    
        chat_id=$(echo $update | jq -r ".message.chat.id") 
        
        get_feedback_reply "$update"
    
        result=$(curl -s "${tele_url}/sendMessage" \n                  --data-urlencode "chat_id=${chat_id}" \n                  --data-urlencode "reply_to_message_id=${message_id}" \n                  --data-urlencode "text=$return_feedback"
            );

        last_id=$(($last_id + 1))            
        echo $last_id > $last_id_file
        
        echo -e "
: ${text}"
    done
}

function get_feedback_reply() {
  # global-module  : return_feedback
    local update=$1
    
    text=$(echo $update | jq -r ".message.text")   
  local first_word=$(echo $text | head -n 1 | awk '{print $1;}')
  
  return_feedback='Good message !'
  case $first_word in
        '/id') 
            username=$(echo $update | jq -r ".message.chat.username")
            return_feedback="You are the mighty @${username}"
        ;;
        *)
            return_feedback='Thank you for your message.'            
        ;;
    esac
}```

    while [[ -n "${!OPTIND}" ]]; do

                exit;;
        esac

        shift $OPTIND
        OPTIND=1
    done
}```

**options.bash**

```#!/usr/bin/env bash

# handling command
function handle_command_plain() {
  local command=$1

    case "$command" in
        version)   
            message_version
            exit;;
    esac
}

# handling -command
function handle_command_opt() {
  local command=$1
  
    case "$command" in
        -)
            handle_command_optarg "$OPTARG"
            ;;
         h)  
            message_usage
            exit;;
         v)  
            message_version
            exit;;
         *)  
            # Invalid Option
            message_usage
            exit;;
    esac
}

# handling --command
function handle_command_optarg() {
  local command=$1
  
    case "$command" in
        version) 
            message_version
            exit;;
        help) 
            message_usage
            exit;;
        observe)
            do_observe
            exit;;
        reply)
            loop_reply
            exit;;
        *) 
            # Invalid Option
            message_usage
            exit;;
    esac
}

function get_options_from_arguments() {  
  # get argument length  
  [[ $# -eq "0" ]] && message_usage && exit;
   
    # ! : indirect expansion
    while [[ -n "${!OPTIND}" ]]; do
        handle_command_plain "${!OPTIND}"

        while getopts "vh-:" OPT; do
             handle_command_opt "$OPT"
        done

        shift $OPTIND
        OPTIND=1
    done
    
    # Invalid Option
    message_usage
    exit
}```

Bahkan kita bisa uji coba Makefile, untuk deploy script yang kita bikin ke dalam OS. Jadinya script kita dapat dipanggil secara __system wide__.

Tetunya lebih nyaman memanggil dari path mana saja sebai berikut:

```% cupubot --help```

Dibandingkan haru bolak-balik baca path.

```% ~/Documents/cupubot/bash/main.bash --help```
Untuk sebetulnya yag kita perlukan adalah meng-copy berkas ke `/usr/local/bin` secara otomatis.
Jadi ada source berkas file.\nDan ada path, destination tempat file akan diletakkan.

Sekarang mari kita lihat source-nya dahulu.

```% ls
Makefile         cupubot-bash   modular-tutorial
config.bash      main.bash      options.bash
controller.bash  messages.bash  tasks```

Perhatikan ada drectory task yang isinya:

``` % ls -l ./tasks/*
-rw-r--r-- 1 epsi users 3530 Jan 28 08:35 ./tasks/logger_html.bash
-rw-r--r-- 1 epsi users 2029 Jan 28 08:41 ./tasks/logger_text.bash
-rw-r--r-- 1 epsi users 2018 Jan 28 12:45 ./tasks/new_member.bash
-rw-r--r-- 1 epsi users  325 Jan 28 07:52 ./tasks/observe.bash
-rw-r--r-- 1 epsi users 1839 Jan 28 08:14 ./tasks/reply.bash```

Di situ ada berkas baru selain `main.bash` yaitu `cupubot-bash` yang isinya sebagaimana berikut:

**cupubot-bash**

```#!/usr/bin/env bash
# redirect script to library

DIR=$(dirname "$0")
DIR=${DIR}/../lib/cupubot
. ${DIR}/main.bash```

`cupubot-bash` inilah satu2nya berkas yang diletakkan ke `/usr/local/bin`. Sisanya ke `/usr/local/lib`.

Itu baru awalnya.

Kita perlu mendefiniskan arah dan tujuan.

```    /usr/local/bin: cupubot-bash

    /usr/local/lib: *.bash```

Menjalankan perlu pakai `sudo`

```% sudo make install

# Libs```

```% sudo make uninstall
Uninstalling...

    done
    
    # Invalid Option
    message_usage
    exit
}```
Mainkan di `$command` yang ada di dalam fungsi `handle_command_plain()`.

function content_event_interval() {

Â Â Â Â # endless loop

Â Â Â Â while :; do 

Â Â Â Â Â Â date +$'interval	%H:%M:%S'

Â Â Â Â Â Â sleep 3

# main


{

Â Â Â Â content_event_idle &

Â Â Â Â 

Â Â Â Â content_event_interval &

Â Â Â Â 

} | while read event; do

Perangkat lunak atau peranti lunak  (bahasa Inggris: software) adalah istilah khusus untuk data yang diformat, dan disimpan secara digital, termasuk program komputer, dokumentasinya, dan berbagai informasi yang bisa dibaca, dan ditulis oleh komputer. ini scriptnya :

```#!/bin/bash

if [[ $# -lt 1 ]]; then
  echo ""
  echo "cara pakai : $0 "pake tanda kutip ya""
  echo ""

  exit 212
fi

VAR=$1
N_CHAR=$(echo ${#VAR})

echo ""
echo "inital string = $VAR"
echo "jumlah character =  $N_CHAR"
echo ""

if [[ $(expr $N_CHAR % 2) -eq 0 ]];then
  echo "jumlah char genap";
  echo "NGGAK ditambahin "z""
else
  VAR=$VAR"z";
  echo "ganjil, jadi $VAR"
fi

echo ""
echo "chacter akhir = $VAR"
echo "dipecah jadi dua pasang :"

echo $VAR |fold -w2|

echo ""
echo "processing"
echo $VAR |fold -w2| while read -r couple; do
  TOTAL=0

  echo "yang di process = $couple"
  N1=$(printf "%d" '$(echo $couple| cut -c1))
  N2=$(printf "%d" '$(echo $couple| cut -c2))
  TOTAL=$((N1+N2));

  echo "ascii char1 = $N1"
  echo "ascii char2 = $N2"
  echo "total = $TOTAL"
  echo ""
done```
itu kayaknya basic command semua, yang baru buat saya itu yang nyeplit jadi dua pasang, sama ngonvert jadi ascii.

kalo konsepnya kan sesuai requirement tadi. kurang lebih begini :

- user minta supaya dihitung jumlah character yang dimasukkan.
variabel dan command yang dipakai :
`N_CHAR=$(echo ${#VAR})`

- setelah input di dapat, tadi user minta di cek, apakah ganjil atau genap.
filtering yang dipakai berarti modulo, kalo habis dibagi dua berarti genap
kalo ndak habis, berarti ganjil, itu peran dari baris `if` :
`$(expr $N_CHAR % 2) -eq 0`

- setelah itu user minta di split jadi dua.
oke, kita split , command yang digunakan :
`fold -w2`

- setelah itu user minta diconvert jadi ascii, trus kalo ndak salah di total sekalian angka asciinya
setelah dapet list yang di split, trus kita ambil per couple pake loop `while ... do ... done`

- di dalem `while .. do .. done`,  kita pisahin tuh couple, pakenya
`cut -c1` sama `cut -c2`, habis tu kita convert jadi, trus di total

# I-EXTRACTOR (beta) (icon extractor android app)
# by Hendriyawan (GDEV)
# 28 Nov 2017
# usage
# sh i-extractor.sh -p <package app>
# sh i-extractor.sh -f file.apk
r='\x1b[1;31m'
g='\x1b[1;32m'
b='\x1b[1;34m'
y='\x1b[1;33m'
c='\x1b[1;36m'
d='\x1b[0m'

function err(){ mesg="$*"; echo -e "${r}*${d} $mesg";}
function proc(){ mesg="$*"; echo -e "${b}*${d} $mesg";}
function succ(){ mesg="$*"; echo -e "${g}*${d} $mesg";}
#print banner
function banner(){
    echo ""
    echo -e "${c}          I-EXTRACTOR${d}"
    echo "             (BETA)"
    echo ""
}
#print usage / help
function usage(){ #print usage / help
    err "usage : i-extractor <options> <package/file>"
    err "options are :"
    echo "	-p, --package : enter package of app"
    echo "	-f, --file    : enter file of .apk
"
}
#check binary busybox & aapt
if [ "$(which aapt)" == "" ] || [ "$(which busybox)" == "" ]; then
    banner
    err "this script need aapt & busybox binary"
    err "IF you're device have rooted, install it to /system/bin"
    err "IF your're device non rooted, install to HOME/bin
"
    exit 1
else
    alias unzip='busybox unzip'
    umask 022
fi

#strip
function strip(){
    local STRING=${1#$"$2"}
    echo ${STRING%"$2"}
}
#extract icon
function extract_icon(){
    banner
    apk_file="$1"
    if [ -z "$apk_file" ]; then
        usage
        exit 1
    elif [ ! -f "$apk_file" ]; then
        usage
        exit 1
    else
        icons="$(aapt dump badging $apk_file | grep application-icon | cut -d : -f 2)"
        succ "apk file : $apk_file"
        for icon in $icons; do
            proc "extracting $icon"
            unzip -o $apk_file $(echo $(strip "${icon}" "'")) &>/dev/null
            unzip -o $apk_file $(echo $(strip "${icon}" "'")) &>/dev/null
        done
        succ "extract done !
"
    fi
}
if [ "$1" == "-p" ] || [ "$1" == "--package" ]; then
    #check file if found
    file="$(pm path $2 | cut -d : -f 2)"
    if [ ! -f $file ]; then
        err "unknow package name : $file !
"
        exit 1
    else
        extract_icon $file
    fi
elif [ "$1" == "-f" ] || [ "$1" == "--file" ]; then
    #check file if found
    file="$2"
    if [ ! -f $file ]; then
        err "no such file or directory : $file !
"
        exit 1
    else
        extract_icon $file
    fi
else
    banner
    err "unknow options !"
    usage
    exit 1
fi

If you're a newbie, you do not want to get into Kali Linux. All the tools that Kali has can be installed on pretty much all mainstream distributions.

If you really want to use Kali, use it in a VM. It is not meant to be your host OS as it is terribly insecure.
